CRITICAL FIX NEEDED: LCM Memory and Self-Iteration are BROKEN

modelab is ABSOLUTELY supposed to remember, get better, and improve using LCM methodology. The X posts described the current broken state as if it were expected behavior — IT IS NOT. This must be fixed.

BROKEN (per GLM audit):
1. LCM-style memory: flat SQLite log, no hierarchical summarization, no token budget management
2. Self-iteration: iterations are independent repeats, no learning between runs

REQUIRED FIXES (priority order):
1. LCM-style hierarchical memory — summarization + expansion + token budget management
2. Self-iteration — LLM analyzes results → refined prompts for next iteration
3. Cross-run learning — store what worked, apply it to future arms

PUBLISH GATE: README/CHANGELOG must reflect all changes in this version cycle.
